rn - Bulk Rename
Bulk rename by editing a file in your editor

Installation:
        make install

Usage: ./rn [-h] [-r <path>] [-a] [-c] [<path>]
        -h, --help      Show this help message
        -r, --revert    Revert the last rename operation in <path>
        -a              Include hidden files in the listing
        -c              Show a confirm prompt before renaming
        <path>          The directory to perform the bulk rename on (default: .)

Example:
        EDITOR=nvim rn -c ~/Desktop
